MongoDB, is the database technology for storing and retrieving data for your applications.

To learn MongoDB, you should have a basic understanding of how databases work and how to use SQL queries. 

- [ ]  **Database Structure:** Databases, Collections, Documents
- [ ]  **CRUD Operations:** Create (insert), Read (find), Update, Delete
- [ ]  **Data Modeling:** Schemas, Document Relationships
- [ ]  **Indexing:** Single Field, Multikey, Text-Based
- [ ]  **Querying:** Filtering and Sorting Data
- [ ]  **Aggregation:** Performing Calculations and Grouping Data
- [ ]  **Security:** Authentication and Authorization
- [ ]  **Replication and Sharding:** Scalability and Availability

